      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that a secular state is inherently more just than one that accommodates religious values is a liberal fantasy. In reality, the real danger is when the government starts imposing its own values on everyone else, as in the case of Roe v. Wade or same-sex marriage. The key is to find a balance between accommodating diverse values and protecting fundamental human rights, but that balance is often a subjective one that can be manipulated by those in power.",
